In [9]:
df['age'] = [i if i.isdigit() else None for i in df['age'] ]
df['sex'] = [ i if  i == 'female' or i == 'male' else None for i in df['sex']]
df['smoker'] = [1 if  i == 'yes' else 0 if i == 'no' else None for i in df['smoker']]
df['region'] = [i if i in ['southwest', 'southeast', 'northwest', 'northeast'] else None for i in df['region']]
In [10]:
df_Submission['sex'] = [ i if  i == 'female' or i == 'male' else None for i in df_Submission['sex']]
df_Submission['smoker'] = [1 if  i == 'yes' else 0 if i == 'no' else None for i in df_Submission['smoker']]
df_Submission['region'] = [i if i in ['southwest', 'southeast', 'northwest', 'northeast'] else None for i in df_Submission['region']]
In [11]:
df['charges'] = [float(i) if i.replace('.','').isdigit() else None for i in df['charges']]
df['charges'] = np.round(np.array(df['charges']))

Bar Charts¶

In [30]:
def find_label(column, size):
    group =  column.unique()
    i = 0
    while len(column[column == group[i]]) != size:
      i += 1 
    return group[i]

relevant = ['AgeGroup', 'sex', 'BMIGroup', 'children', 'smoker', 'region']

for x in relevant:
  xArray = df2.groupby(x)[x].size()
  previousSum = 0
  for i in range(len(xArray)):
    plt.bar([x], xArray[i], bottom = previousSum , 
            label = find_label(df2[x], xArray[i]))
    plt.text(relevant.index(x)-0.15,previousSum+20, str(xArray[i]))
    previousSum += xArray[i]
plt.title('A Brief Look at the Data')
plt.gcf().set_size_inches(10, 10)
plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0), ncol = 1,
              loc='lower left', fontsize='small');
b = plt.gcf()
plt.close()

Multiple Linear Regression Model¶

Storing and plotting the mean squared error for 10 runs

In [46]:
mseLinR = []

LR = LinearRegression()

for i in range(10):
  xtrain, xtest, ytrain, ytest = train_test_split(x_scaled, y_scaled)
  LR.fit(xtrain, ytrain)
  yp = LR.predict(xtest)
  mseLinR.append(mean_squared_error(ytest, yp))

Decision Tree Model¶

In [50]:
from sklearn import tree
In [51]:
def runTree (depth):
  clf = tree.DecisionTreeRegressor(max_depth=depth)
  mseTree = []

  for i in range(10):
    xtrain, xtest, ytrain, ytest = train_test_split(x_scaled, y_scaled)
    clf.fit(xtrain, ytrain)
    yp = clf.predict(xtest)
    mseTree.append(mean_squared_error(ytest, yp))

  return mseTree

KNeighbors Regressor¶

In [63]:
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsRegressor
In [64]:
def runKNR (n):
  neigh = KNeighborsRegressor(n_neighbors=n)
  mseKNR = []

  for i in range(10):
    xtrain, xtest, ytrain, ytest = train_test_split(x_scaled, y_scaled)
    neigh = neigh.fit(xtrain, ytrain)
    yp = neigh.predict(xtest)
    mseKNR.append(mean_squared_error(ytest, yp))

  return mseKNR
In [65]:

  mseKNRs.append(runKNR(i))
